Brother...

11
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:09,200
That's a shame.

12
00:02:12,950 --> 00:02:16,400
If I had cut you any deeper, your arm would have fallen off.

13
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,680
You're not that good, eh?

14
00:02:21,150 --> 00:02:23,400
Try harder.

15
00:02:39,590 --> 00:02:42,280
Oh, that attack was quite sharp.

16
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:45,770
But what can you do? I totally avoided it.

17
00:02:45,770 --> 00:02:48,650
You... I can see all of it.

18
00:02:48,650 --> 00:02:49,320
What?

19
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:51,600
I can see all of your attacks.

20
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:53,740
Crazy bastard.

21
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:28,970
Gil Tae Mi, you bastard!

22
00:04:28,970 --> 00:04:32,340
Accept the Heaven's punishment, you bastard!

23
00:04:34,580 --> 00:04:36,360
Damn it.

24
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:40,000
I...
 (Gil Tae Mi) 

25
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,690
What did I do wrong?

26
00:04:44,020 --> 00:04:46,340
You bastard!

27
00:04:46,340 --> 00:04:50,240
You have always stepped on weak people and stolen from them.

28
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,710
Hey.

29
00:04:57,790 --> 00:05:02,970
Of course, I would step on the weak. Would I step on the strong?

30
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:05,930
I would also steal from the weak.

31
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:09,650
Are you telling me to steal from the strong?

32
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:29,000
Since the world began,

33
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:36,080
the weak have always been stepped on by the strong.

34
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:43,680
Even a thousand years ago, even a thousand years from now!

35
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:48,820
The strong steal from the weak.

36
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:51,880
In this world,

37
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:57,040
the only truth is that the strong

38
00:05:57,040 --> 00:06:01,880
take and swallow the weak.

39
00:06:04,980 --> 00:06:07,270
The strong

40
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:10,490
step on

41
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:14,050
and steal from the weak.

42
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:30,010
This is the only constant

43
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:34,220
truth!

44
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:42,630
So let's hurry and fight.

45
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:46,150
The strong

46
00:07:48,030 --> 00:07:50,030
take and swallow

47
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:55,850
the weak. Like this.

48
00:07:56,570 --> 00:08:03,740
♫  Why do you cry so sadly?  ♫

49
00:08:05,540 --> 00:08:07,730
What is your name?

50
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:16,730
I have to at least know who killed me.

51
00:08:17,530 --> 00:08:19,130
I...

52
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:23,240
I

53
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:27,820
am the best swordsman of the Three Kingdoms!

54
00:08:31,730 --> 00:08:34,100
Lee Bang Ji.

55
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:36,090
Brother.

56
00:08:38,340 --> 00:08:44,490
♫  Ask the world  ♫

57
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:50,060
♫  Politics that distinguishes life and death  ♫

58
00:08:50,060 --> 00:08:52,140
Lee Bang Ji...

59
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:59,880
♫  What's the difference of the sword  ♫

60
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:02,790
Gil Tae Mi has died! Gil Tae Mi has died!

61
00:09:02,790 --> 00:09:05,180
That warrior killed Gil Tae Mi!

62
00:09:05,180 --> 00:09:06,800
He's the new best swordsman of the Three Kingdoms!

63
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:09,700
 Lee Bang Ji 

64
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:41,360
 Brother... Are you going like that?
(Gil Sun Mi) 

65
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:48,760
 Fortunately, in your last moments, you were not a corrupt official but a swordsman. 

66
00:09:51,980 --> 00:09:56,020
 I hope the you now rest in peace. 

67
00:10:13,820 --> 00:10:16,690
Manse! Manse!

68
00:10:41,420 --> 00:10:46,720
 The people... The people are smiling. 

69
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:51,300
 Arrest all of Hong In Bang and Gil Tae Mi's remaining people. 

70
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:54,180
 Transfer them to the investigation office! 

71
00:10:54,180 --> 00:11:00,880
 Also, the lands that they have stolen will all be returned to their original owners. 

72
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:06,720
 The falsely accused people will be released and returned to their previous occupations. 

73
00:11:12,390 --> 00:11:13,450
Why are you doing this?

74
00:11:13,450 --> 00:11:17,920
We are here to transfer Hong In Bang's informant, Jeok Ryong, to the investigation office.

75
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:22,620
Those who resist will be charged with a severe crime according to the national law.

76
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:28,100
Ah.

77
00:11:31,710 --> 00:11:34,290
You don't have to do this.

78
00:11:34,290 --> 00:11:36,430
Let's go to the investigation office.

79
00:11:36,430 --> 00:11:39,070
- Tie him up.
- Yes!

80
00:11:40,940 --> 00:11:45,390
 If I only knew beforehand that Hong In Bang wouldn't last long...
(Jeok Ryong: Bi Guk Temple's Head Monk) 

81
00:11:45,390 --> 00:11:48,660
 Why did I hesitate like this... 

82
00:11:54,340 --> 00:11:57,180
So you got a government position again.

83
00:11:57,180 --> 00:11:59,210
That's what happened.

84
00:11:59,210 --> 00:12:03,170
We were also together when you first got a government position.
 (Hong In Bang) 

85
00:12:03,170 --> 00:12:07,810
Yes. Why did you do it?

86
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:15,010
Forget the rattle talk and tell me honestly.
 (Sam Bong: Jeong Do Jeon) 

87
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:22,410
Why did a person like you, who had good education and knows the ways of a Confucian scholar, do this?

88
00:12:23,330 --> 00:12:25,030
Mencius was wrong.

89
00:12:25,030 --> 00:12:26,550
What?

90
00:12:26,550 --> 00:12:33,480
Mencius said so. Benevolence means that when a child goes crawling to a well, you would save him even if he's not your own.

91
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,330
That is human nature.

92
00:12:35,330 --> 00:12:36,570
Isn't it?

93
00:12:36,570 --> 00:12:42,610
But if it's for your benefit, throwing the child into the well is also being human.

94
00:12:42,610 --> 00:12:45,420
During troubled times like this, it's something we've seen a lot.

95
00:12:45,420 --> 00:12:48,500
Humans are weak and selfish.

96
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:54,600
From the people to politicians—everyone.  I was just the same.

97
00:12:55,350 --> 00:12:58,330
The whole time I was tortured and sent to exile,

98
00:12:58,330 --> 00:13:01,790
the Confucian scholar ways that I had learned for half of my life disappeared

99
00:13:01,790 --> 00:13:06,550
and only suspicion and uneasiness remained.

100
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:13,380
Am I going to end like this? Didn't everyone abandon me? Is there not a thing that will go according to plan?

101
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:17,770
The paved benevolence, righteousness, courtesy, and wisdom powerlessly disappeared.

102
00:13:17,770 --> 00:13:23,070
As much as you know, fear makes you tremble and doubt.

103
00:13:23,070 --> 00:13:26,530
That's our nature as educated people.

104
00:13:26,530 --> 00:13:29,850
So that's how you rationalize it.

105
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:35,930
Rationalize? That's right. Because I have to live.

106
00:13:35,930 --> 00:13:38,220
"It's all a lie. Humans are originally like this."

107
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:46,050
"This country called Goryeo has been hopeless for so long."

108
00:13:46,050 --> 00:13:52,770
And this is true. Even if it wasn't me, this country

109
00:13:55,310 --> 00:13:57,610
is hopeless.

110
00:13:59,370 --> 00:14:01,630
We need to go to the execution grounds.

111
00:14:02,890 --> 00:14:09,030
You'll probably raise this country up now.

112
00:14:09,030 --> 00:14:10,940
But,

113
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:15,200
will it work?

114
00:14:19,540 --> 00:14:26,560


115
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:15,620
Why? Do you want to debate some more?

116
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:19,480
You probably want to object, right?

117
00:15:21,350 --> 00:15:25,860
But what can we do? We don't have the time.

118
00:15:25,860 --> 00:15:27,790
No.

119
00:15:27,790 --> 00:15:31,980
I realized something good from your words.

120
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:34,580
I will make good use of it.

121
00:15:34,580 --> 00:15:35,750
Do as you wish.

122
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:42,450
Also, there are also some parts of what you said that I completely agree with.

123
00:15:42,450 --> 00:15:44,670
What are they?

124
00:15:49,850 --> 00:15:53,210
"Goryeo is already

125
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:57,530
hopeless."

126
00:16:05,350 --> 00:16:06,530
What?

127
00:16:06,530 --> 00:16:13,750
I'm not even interested in raising this Goryeo up again.

128
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:18,240
Could you be...

129
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:24,700
If there really is an afterlife, make sure to watch. Goodbye, Brother.

130
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:41,260
Start the execution!

131
00:17:32,730 --> 00:17:36,590
 How... How is that guy still alive?
(Boon Yi) 

132
00:17:48,790 --> 00:17:51,150
Why do you look like that?

133
00:17:51,150 --> 00:17:57,520
He's still the Elder I have served for so long. To see him go like that...

134
00:17:57,520 --> 00:18:02,860
Ho! This man just says what he wants.

135
00:18:02,860 --> 00:18:06,250
Although it was only because of Hong In Bang's orders,
 (Jo Min Soo) 

136
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:09,510
the crimes you committed while being his servant...

137
00:18:09,510 --> 00:18:11,840
I am gravely sorry.

138
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:20,950
What? What did you say?

139
00:18:20,950 --> 00:18:24,290
I said that I think you are really cool, Young Master!

140
00:18:24,290 --> 00:18:26,100
What are you saying all of a sudden?

141
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:30,560
At first, I thought you were just a noble who was good at studying and had a way with words.
 (Moo Hyul) 

142
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:36,520
But you get more amazing in the long run. You look like someone who will make it big. You are an outstanding person!

143
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:41,510
Ah, seriously... It's an undeniable fact.
 (Lee Bang Won) 

144
00:18:41,510 --> 00:18:42,450
But why all of a sudden?

145
00:18:42,450 --> 00:18:44,290
At the Ilwol Jeong pavillion,

146
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:49,620
was it Haedong Gapjok? Anyway, you placed the gunpowder in front of those people.

147
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:55,760
Wow... Really. After that day, my heart wouldn't stop racing.

148
00:18:55,760 --> 00:19:00,860
In the end,  you got the King's orders with that signed letter and overthrew Hong In Bang and Gil Tae Mi.

149
00:19:00,860 --> 00:19:04,300
Even if other people don't know, I surely know it.

150
00:19:05,350 --> 00:19:09,730
Today at the market, I saw people smiling brightly.

151
00:19:10,590 --> 00:19:15,590
I've always thought that the reason why I always walk around smiling is because I am lacking.

152
00:19:15,590 --> 00:19:20,950
But other people appear to know how to smile too.

153
00:19:21,850 --> 00:19:26,890
It's my first time seeing people gathered like that and smiling.

154
00:19:26,890 --> 00:19:29,570
You made it like that, Young Master.

155
00:19:29,570 --> 00:19:35,650
Well, if I think of it like you do, then that is true.

156
00:19:35,650 --> 00:19:38,030
But why are you saying such things all of a sudden?

157
00:19:38,030 --> 00:19:43,030
I... want to sincerely protect you.

158
00:19:43,030 --> 00:19:51,230
I will protect you, and in the moments when I see the people smiling in the world you're going to make, it will be worth it.

159
00:19:51,230 --> 00:19:56,430
So please officially make me your bodyguard.

160
00:19:56,430 --> 00:19:58,470
You've always been my bodyguard.

161
00:19:58,470 --> 00:20:00,510
Ahh, but those are just jokes.

162
00:20:00,510 --> 00:20:05,750
Buk Doo second rank, whatever... I know that such a thing doesn't exist. Make it official.

163
00:20:05,750 --> 00:20:12,810
You are my bodyguard. From the beginning, you've always been my bodyguard.

164
00:20:14,820 --> 00:20:22,110
You are the first person I ever gave my sword to. What does this sword mean?

165
00:20:23,150 --> 00:20:30,560
It's a weapon. Giving this to you means I trust you.

166
00:20:30,560 --> 00:20:32,150
Really?

167
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:39,970
What are you doing? Are you not going?

168
00:20:42,740 --> 00:20:44,120
I'm going.

169
00:20:49,340 --> 00:20:53,070
What are you doing? My bodyguard

170
00:20:53,070 --> 00:20:54,870
is not following me?

171
00:20:54,870 --> 00:20:56,490
Yes, my Lord.

172
00:21:31,770 --> 00:21:34,580
Teacher, this is...

173
00:21:34,580 --> 00:21:38,080
Hong In Bang is right. Because the Sadaebu are afraid of leadership being taken from them,

174
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:42,050
they don't know that they are a bunch of people who doubt, check, get jealous, and try to win against each other.

175
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:43,460
So?

176
00:21:43,460 --> 00:21:47,070
What kind of idea did you get?

177
00:21:47,070 --> 00:21:51,580
I was also like that. During my exile, I was always anxious about being forgotten.

178
00:21:52,930 --> 00:21:57,430
Why did a person, who found what he has to do there and wanted to help the people, become anxious and uneasy?

179
00:21:57,430 --> 00:22:00,370
We are the same as the Sadaebu.

180
00:22:00,370 --> 00:22:03,830
But Mencius left a group like that in charge of the country. Why did he do that?

181
00:22:03,830 --> 00:22:04,980
Did Mencius not know?

182
00:22:04,980 --> 00:22:08,830
No, Mencius knew about that and emphasized benevolence.

183
00:22:08,830 --> 00:22:12,730
But I can't trust just benevolence.

184
00:22:12,730 --> 00:22:17,250
That's why I will make the Sadaebu's doubts into a system.

185
00:22:17,250 --> 00:22:22,710
I will make a system out of their envy, jealousy, and greed for victory and tearing people now.

186
00:22:22,710 --> 00:22:25,020
I will make the Saheonbu that always doubts.
 (Saheonbu: office in charge of judicial responsibilities) 

187
00:22:25,020 --> 00:22:29,680
I will make the Saganwon that always reprimands and the Hongmungwan that always chatters.
 (Saganwon: office that criticizes the King's faults, Hongmungwan: office that advises the King) 

188
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:31,490
The Sadaebu to the King and the King to the Sadaebu.

189
00:22:31,490 --> 00:22:33,710
Also, so that the Sadaebu keep each other in check,

190
00:22:33,710 --> 00:22:36,850
so that there's no other choice but to stop decay and corruption,

191
00:22:36,850 --> 00:22:39,280
I need to make a bureaucratic cabinet like that.

192
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:44,650
Are you talking about a system that monopolizes the country even if there is uncertainty and criticism?

193
00:22:44,650 --> 00:22:46,230
That's right.

194
00:22:46,230 --> 00:22:53,580
Like that, the evil that was born from the nature of doubt and criticism won't transmit to the people.

195
00:22:56,320 --> 00:23:04,290
 Clockwise: King-Saheonbu-Hongmungwan-Saganwon 

196
00:23:04,290 --> 00:23:09,850
 Doubting and keeping each other in check 

197
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:15,860
 What does this all mean? 

198
00:23:15,860 --> 00:23:19,150
 Is that... possible? 

199
00:23:19,150 --> 00:23:20,890
 What about the people? 

200
00:23:20,890 --> 00:23:25,250
 Is there a way for the people to keep them in check as well? 

201
00:23:25,250 --> 00:23:28,730
 I want it. All of this. 

202
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:40,880
 It's just... ability and talent that I can't compete with. 

203
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:45,940
 In the end... I couldn't understand a thing they said. 

204
00:23:51,580 --> 00:23:52,640
Why are you like that?

205
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:55,060
What about you?

206
00:23:56,130 --> 00:23:57,870
You know...

207
00:23:57,870 --> 00:24:01,880
You also didn't understand a thing, did you?

208
00:24:06,640 --> 00:24:09,040
I live because of you.

209
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:13,160
What?

210
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:24,740
Now that everything has been wrapped up, I came to extend my gratitude for our deal last time.

211
00:24:25,670 --> 00:24:33,040
Because of our deal, I got the King's orders, overthrew the Do Dang triumvirate, and state affairs have totally changed.

212
00:24:34,060 --> 00:24:39,500
If not for your help, it wouldn't have been possible. I sincerely thank you.

213
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:42,810
I heard about how you received the signed letters.
 (Min Da Kyung: Future Queen Wongyeong) 

214
00:24:42,810 --> 00:24:47,460
It was perplexing but still amazing.

215
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:52,060
In regards to that, I will offer my late apologies to Father-in-law.

216
00:24:52,060 --> 00:24:55,960
I didn't disclose your family's secret to my father.

217
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:59,580
I told you about it because I trust your judgement.

218
00:24:59,580 --> 00:25:02,980
How are you advancing so far?

219
00:25:05,960 --> 00:25:08,640
What kind of authority are you putting together?

220
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:12,160
A political alliance between General Lee Seong Gye and General Choi Yeong will probably be formed now.

221
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:16,750
That person will never approve of this plan. What are you going to do?

222
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:29,380
I'm sorry. I was rushing you.

223
00:25:29,380 --> 00:25:32,410
Slowly tell me about it.

224
00:25:32,410 --> 00:25:34,320
Then, have a rest.

225
00:25:42,420 --> 00:25:47,770
Hong In Bang, Gil Tae Mi... They both deserved it after what they have done.

226
00:25:47,770 --> 00:25:51,410
Hey... As I lived through these troubled times,
 (Myo Sang: Moo Hyul's Grandmother) 

227
00:25:51,410 --> 00:25:56,620
I've seen that happen a lot. I saw it first when I was born.

228
00:25:56,620 --> 00:26:01,660
Really... That child Tae Mi was such a nice boy when he was young.
 (Hong Dae Hong: Moo Hyul's Master) 

229
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:05,200
This crybaby. Everyone's nice when they are young.

230
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,220
Where would you find someone who wasn't nice when he or she was young?

231
00:26:07,220 --> 00:26:13,560
Even when he was young, he acted like a girl. He would wear a flower ring and play house.

232
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:21,290
He acted like a girl when he was young and his father thought he was useless so he brought him to me to make him into a man.

233
00:26:21,290 --> 00:26:22,990
Oh my.

234
00:26:22,990 --> 00:26:27,320
It doesn't even suit you so why are you acting like a teacher all of a sudden?

235
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:30,410
I'm just feeling totally refreshed.

236
00:26:30,410 --> 00:26:32,490
Tae Mi, this kid...

237
00:26:33,290 --> 00:26:34,860
Aigoo.

238
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:48,560
You are all grown up now.

239
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:55,100
Hong In Bang.

240
00:26:56,290 --> 00:26:58,230
 Hong In Bang. 

241
00:26:58,230 --> 00:27:02,620
 Hong In Bang. Seonggyungwan Saye.
(government position in charge of guidance) 

242
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:05,440
 What Sam Bong said probably made your heart race. 

243
00:27:05,440 --> 00:27:09,230
 Is that fluttering because of the country that Sam Bong is going to make, 

